      "side": 1,
      "message": "I realized that we can\u0027t use /userinfo at all since it doesn\u0027t return the audience of the token, which means that if I login into some random web site, it can then forward my tokens to LUCI and LUCI will not know how to reject them (they\u0027ll pass /userinfo check just fine).\n\nWith /tokeninfo it is prevented by checking `aud` field in the response, which is OAuth client ID. We have a whitelist of IDs control and trust. Tokens from random web sites will have different client IDs (this is guaranteed by Google\u0027s OAuth2 login flow implementation).\n\nIf /tokeninfo stops working, we are basically dooomed.",
